Class GraphEngine

java.lang.Object
  graph.GraphEngine
All Implemented Interfaces:
IFlightGraph
public class GraphEngine
extends java.lang.Object
implements IFlightGraph

Class used to get flight and routes information from the flight graph.

Provides methods for finding direct fights, finding out if there is a route between airports, and getting all the routes from an airport.

Author:
Richard Walker

getRoutesDir

public java.util.ArrayList<java.util.LinkedList<org.graphstream.graph.Edge>> getRoutesDir(Airport depPort,
                                                                                          Airport arrPort,
                                                                                          int maxFlights,
                                                                                          boolean isFirstClass)
Gets all the routes in a general direction between two airports, with a provided number of flights. You must specify the maximum of flights the route can have.

The routes returned will be heading towards the final destination in some logical manner.

E.g. ORD (Chicago) -> SFO (San Fransico) would go in a western direction.

Parameters:
depPort - the departure airport
arrPort - the arrival airport
maxFlights - the maximum number of flights the route can have
isFirstClass - true if you are searching for First Class flights
Returns:
a list of all the possible routes in that general direction.
